 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Wisconsin Blue Flame Council cited an incremental unit cost of $150 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to $200 to add automatic ignition devices and flue dampers to residential gas-fired water heaters. (Wisconsin Blue
Flame Council, No. 33 at 33). Equitable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Resources stated the additional cost for electrical safety controls to be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approximately $20 to $50. (Equitable Resources, No. 72 at 2). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Department used an incremental material cost of $49 for a spark 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ignition system, flue damper, 24-volt plug-transformer, and control relay.
<FOOTCITE>18</FOOTCITE>
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Other factory costs were from the Gas Appliance Manufacturers Association 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
data.
